10px;">
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><strong>Programming note:</strong><em> Money S=
tuff will be off tomorrow and Monday, back on Tuesday.</em></p>
<table class=3D"header" width=3D"100%" border=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" cellp=
adding=3D"0">
<tr>
<td class=3D"body-header-container" style=3D"border-collapse: collapse; mso=
-table-lspace: 0pt; mso-table-rspace: 0pt;">
<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">MMTLP</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CHe who sells what isn=E2=80=99t his=
=E2=80=99n, must buy it back <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness=
.com/click/31735317.259418/aHR0cHM6Ly9lbi53aWtpcGVkaWEub3JnL3dpa2kvRGFuaWVs=
X0RyZXc/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB1db19730" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=
=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: =
none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; bo=
rder-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> or go to prison</a>,=E2=
=80=9D which sometimes gives people bad ideas. Here is=C2=A0the bad idea:</=
p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">If people sell stock short, they have=
 to borrow the stock from a stock lender, and return it when they are done.=
 They borrow the stock, they sell it, they wait, and then they buy it back =
to return to the lender. (The short sellers hope that the stock goes down b=
etween when they sell it and when they buy it.)</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-=
bottom: 5px;">If the stock pays a dividend, the short sellers have to pay t=
he dividend back to the stock lender.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5p=
x;">If the stock somehow becomes=C2=A0<em>not tradable</em>, then the short=
 sellers can=E2=80=99t buy it back to deliver to their lenders, and they ar=
e stuck, bwahahahahaha, prison!</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">If=
 the stock pays a dividend that is not cash or regular stock, but rather so=
me weird thing that is=C2=A0<em>not tradable</em>, then the short sellers c=
an=E2=80=99t get the dividend to deliver to their lenders, and they are stu=
ck,=C2=A0bwahahahahaha, prison!</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And so if you are a certain sort of public com=
pany chief executive officer, you might spend=C2=A0time thinking about ques=
tions like =E2=80=9Chow can I make my stock not tradable=E2=80=9D or =E2=80=
=9Chow can I pay my shareholders a dividend that is not tradable,=E2=80=9D =
because if you can crack that nut then the people who have sold your stock =
short will be marched off to prison and you will have won.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I=E2=80=99m sorry, this is so dumb. If you are=
 a public company chief executive officer and your main goal, or even one o=
f your top five goals, is punishing short sellers, then you have already lo=
st. That=E2=80=99s a terrible goal! The way to deal with short sellers is t=
o run a good business that makes a lot of money; this will make your stock =
go up, and the shorts will take care of themselves. Short sellers don=E2=80=
=99t matter! They can=E2=80=99t hurt you! At most, they can make your stock=
 go down a bit, but your business does not depend on your stock price; your=
 business depends on your business. Just do your business! Ignore the short=
s.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">There are two exceptions to this<a class=3D"fo=
otnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-1" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration=
: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; =
border-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: transparent !import=
ant; display: inline-block;">
<span>[1]</span>
</a>:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">If you are <a href=3D"https://link.ma=
il.bloombergbusiness.com/click/31735317.259418/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJn=
LmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDUtMjUvdGhlLXVzLW1pZ2h0LWJlLW9ubHktYWE=
_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDYwODIzX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW=
5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjMwNjA4JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ce=
ef4b8524a319a23cBee7b9299" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" t=
arget=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important;=
 border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-styl=
e: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  a bank</a>, then your business depends=
 on confidence, and a declining stock price can undermine confidence. It is=
 sad and undignified when bank CEOs spend a lot of time worrying about shor=
t sellers, but it is=C2=A0<em>understandable</em>.</li>=09<li style=3D"marg=
in-bottom: 5px;">If your business is a pump-and-dump scam, then your busine=
ss really is about the stock price. =E2=80=9CJust run a good business=E2=80=
=9D is absurd advice when your business is putting out press releases to ma=
ke your stock go up, and it does make sense that you would be laser-focused=
 on fighting short sellers.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And so if you are a public company CEO and you=
 spend all your time trying to devise ways to get your short sellers in tro=
uble, that=E2=80=99s just sort of a bad sign?</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In 2019, Overstock.com launched a short squeez=
e. Its idiosyncratic CEO, Patrick Byrne, had a long-running crusade against=
 short sellers and actually notched a few wins over the years. In 2019, he =
decided to destroy the shorts by issuing a special stock dividend on Overst=
ock=E2=80=99s own blockchain platform. Basically each shareholder would get=
 shares of a new class of preferred stock; the preferred stock would be tra=
dable only on Overstock=E2=80=99s blockchain and, more important, it would =
not be tradable <em>at all</em> for six months. This meant that, if you wer=
e short Overstock stock, you=E2=80=99d have to deliver the preferred stock =
to your stock lenders, but you couldn=E2=80=99t deliver the preferred stock=
, because you couldn=E2=80=99t buy it, because it wasn=E2=80=99t tradable. =
Checkmate!</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">No, not checkmate, what actually happened is:<=
/p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: disc; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;">=
=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Short sellers were fine; their lenders=
 agreed to take cash instead of the special preferred stock.</li>=09<li sty=
le=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">The SEC investigated, and short sellers sued, Ov=
erstock for alleged=C2=A0market manipulation from this dividend scheme, tho=
ugh the SEC never brought a case and <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomberg=
business.com/click/31735317.259418/aHR0cHM6Ly9jb2ludGVsZWdyYXBoLmNvbS9uZXdz=
L2NvdXJ0LXRvc3Nlcy1vdXQtc2hvcnQtc2VsbGVycy1sYXdzdWl0LXRhcmdldGluZy1vdmVyc3R=
vY2stcy1kaWdpdGFsLWRpdmlkZW5k/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB8e7668ba" itemprop=
=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #0=
00000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-b=
ottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">=
 the short sellers lost</a>. (To be fair, Overstock had non-short-squeeze-y=
 reasons for doing the dividend; Byrne was really into blockchain stuff.)</=
li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Byrne <a href=3D"https://link.mail.=
bloombergbusiness.com/click/31735317.259418/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmN=
vbS9vcGluaW9uL25ld3NsZXR0ZXJzLzIwMTktMDgtMjMvbW9uZXktc3R1ZmYtb3ZlcnN0b2NrLW=
xvc2VzLWEtc3B5Y2F0Y2hlci1jZW8_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDYwODIzX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZ=
Gl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjMwNjA4JnV0bV9jYW1w=
YWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBc2842f96" itemprop=3D"StoryLi=
nk" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text=
-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color=
: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> resigned a=
s Overstock=E2=80=99s CEO</a> for reasons having to do with a Russian spy, =
I don=E2=80=99t know, it=E2=80=99s very confusing.</li>=09<li style=3D"marg=
in-bottom: 5px;">On his personal blog (<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombe=
rgbusiness.com/click/31735317.259418/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZGVlcGNhcHR1cmUuY29tLw=
/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBcebf6e32" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"ite=
mscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !i=
mportant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bo=
ttom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">DeepCapture.com</a>), Byrne <a =
href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/31735317.259418/aHR0c=
HM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL25ld3NsZXR0ZXJzLzIwMTktMDktMTkvbW9u=
ZXktc3R1ZmYtb3ZlcnN0b2NrLWhhcy1oYWQtYS13aWxkLXdlZWs_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDYwODIzX01=
PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm=
09MjMwNjA4JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBddcc38f=
0" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=
=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: =
1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-c=
olor: #ccc;"> complained about the SEC rescuing short sellers</a> in these =
terms: =E2=80=9CNow, after 15 years of being scofflaws, the shorts are cryi=
ng because they are getting sucked into a black hole they created themselve=
s. If you call =E2=80=98Bazoomba!=E2=80=99 for them now, I am going to use =
this website to vaporize you with information I give the public. I am 100% =
confident that at least one of you knows to what I am referring.=E2=80=9D</=
li>
</ul>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Bazoomba. You would not call all of this an ov=
erwhelming success for Overstock or Byrne. The short sellers were not exact=
ly vanquished. Overstock=E2=80=99s stock fell about 70% between the <a href=
=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/31735317.259418/aHR0cHM6L=
y93d3cuZ2xvYmVuZXdzd2lyZS5jb20vbmV3cy1yZWxlYXNlLzIwMTkvMDcvMzAvMTg5MzY1MS8w=
L2VuL092ZXJzdG9jay1jb20tSW5jLURlY2xhcmVzLURpdmlkZW5kLW9mLU9uZS1EaWdpdGFsLVN=
oYXJlLWZvci1FdmVyeS1UZW4tU2hhcmVzLUhlbGQuaHRtbA/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBff=
61251d" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" st=
yle=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-widt=
h: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgroun=
d-color: #ccc;"> announcement of the special dividend</a>=C2=A0and the end =
of 2019, though it soared again in=C2=A02020 after Byrne left.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On the other hand it was kind of a clever idea=
, and Byrne is not the only CEO to hate short sellers. I can=E2=80=99t say =
there have been a lot of copycats, but for instance AMC Entertainment Holdi=
ngs Inc. has spent some time giving its shareholders weird stuff (<a href=
=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/31735317.259418/aHR0cHM6L=
